#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn6:0.2"
msgid "Mahālisutta "
msgstr "With Mahāli "

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn6:0.3"
msgid "1. Brāhmaṇadūtavatthu "
msgstr "1. On the Brahmin Emissaries "

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli1.150, sc1
msgctxt "dn6:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn6:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

msgctxt "dn6:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā vesāliyaṃ paṭivasanti kenacideva karaṇīyena. "
msgstr "Now at that time several brahmin emissaries from Kosala and Magadha were residing in Vesālī on some business. "

msgctxt "dn6:1.4"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho te kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā: "
msgstr "They heard: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:1.5"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—is staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

msgctxt "dn6:1.6"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "dn6:1.7"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "dn6:1.8"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti. "
msgstr "He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others. "

msgctxt "dn6:1.9"
msgid "So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "dn6:1.10"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2, pts-vp-pli1.151, sc2
msgctxt "dn6:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho te kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā yena mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then they went to the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood to see the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:2.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā nāgito bhagavato upaṭṭhāko hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time Venerable Nāgita was the Buddha’s attendant. "

msgctxt "dn6:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho te kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā yenāyasmā nāgito tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ nāgitaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "The brahmin emissaries went up to him and said, "

msgctxt "dn6:2.4"
msgid "“kahaṃ nu kho, bho nāgita, etarahi so bhavaṃ gotamo viharati? "
msgstr "“Master Nāgita, where is Master Gotama at present? "

msgctxt "dn6:2.5"
msgid "Dassanakāmā hi mayaṃ taṃ bhavantaṃ gotaman”ti. "
msgstr "For we want to see him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:2.6"
msgid "“Akālo kho, āvuso, bhagavantaṃ dassanāya, paṭisallīno bhagavā”ti. "
msgstr "“It’s the wrong time to see the Buddha; he is on retreat.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:2.7"
msgid "Atha kho te kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā tattheva ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu: "
msgstr "So the brahmin emissaries sat down to one side, thinking, "

msgctxt "dn6:2.8"
msgid "“disvāva mayaṃ taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ gamissāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“We’ll go only after we’ve seen Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn6:2.9"
msgid "2. Oṭṭhaddhalicchavīvatthu "
msgstr "2. On Oṭṭhaddha the Licchavi "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, sc3
msgctxt "dn6:3.1"
msgid "Oṭṭhaddhopi licchavī mahatiyā licchavīparisāya saddhiṃ yena mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā yenāyasmā nāgito tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ nāgitaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho oṭṭhaddhopi licchavī āyasmantaṃ nāgitaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Oṭṭhaddha the Licchavi together with a large assembly of Licchavis also approached Nāgita at the hall with the peaked roof. He bowed, stood to one side, and said to Nāgita, "

msgctxt "dn6:3.2"
msgid "“kahaṃ nu kho, bhante nāgita, etarahi so bhagavā viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, "
msgstr "“Master Nāgita, where is the Blessed One at present, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha? "

msgctxt "dn6:3.3"
msgid "dassanakāmā hi mayaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti. "
msgstr "For we want to see him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:3.4"
msgid "“Akālo kho, mahāli, bhagavantaṃ dassanāya, paṭisallīno bhagavā”ti. "
msgstr "“It’s the wrong time to see the Buddha; he is on retreat.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:3.5"
msgid "Oṭṭhaddhopi licchavī tattheva ekamantaṃ nisīdi: "
msgstr "So Oṭṭhaddha also sat down to one side, thinking, "

msgctxt "dn6:3.6"
msgid "“disvāva ahaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ gamissāmi arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti. "
msgstr "“I’ll go only after I’ve seen the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, sc4
msgctxt "dn6:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho sīho samaṇuddeso yenāyasmā nāgito tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ nāgitaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho sīho samaṇuddeso āyasmantaṃ nāgitaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the novice Sīha approached Nāgita. He bowed, stood to one side, and said to Nāgita, "

msgctxt "dn6:4.2"
msgid "“ete, bhante kassapa, sambahulā kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā idhūpasaṅkantā bhagavantaṃ dassanāya; oṭṭhaddhopi licchavī mahatiyā licchavīparisāya saddhiṃ idhūpasaṅkanto bhagavantaṃ dassanāya, sādhu, bhante kassapa, labhataṃ esā janatā bhagavantaṃ dassanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, Kassapa, these several brahmin emissaries from Kosala and Magadha, and also Oṭṭhaddha the Licchavi together with a large assembly of Licchavis, have come here to see the Buddha. It’d be good if these people got to see the Buddha.” "

# NOTE: This basically a textbook example of how not to do your job. Take orders too literally, being inflexible and uncompassionate. Then when given good advice, respond gracelessly, concerned only to avoid possible repercussions. so you fob it off on a junior, so they get any fallback, while you skirt responsibility. No wonder Nagita got replaced!
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.152, sc5
msgctxt "dn6:4.3"
msgid "“Tena hi, sīha, tvaññeva bhagavato ārocehī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, Sīha, tell the Buddha yourself.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:4.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho sīho samaṇuddeso āyasmato nāgitassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho sīho samaṇuddeso bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Sīha. He went to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and told him of the people waiting to see him, adding: "

msgctxt "dn6:4.5"
msgid "“ete, bhante, sambahulā kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā idhūpasaṅkantā bhagavantaṃ dassanāya, oṭṭhaddhopi licchavī mahatiyā licchavīparisāya saddhiṃ idhūpasaṅkanto bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:4.6"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, labhataṃ esā janatā bhagavantaṃ dassanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, it’d be good if these people got to see the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:4.7"
msgid "“Tena hi, sīha, vihārapacchāyāyaṃ āsanaṃ paññapehī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, Sīha, spread out a seat in the shade of the dwelling.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:4.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho sīho samaṇuddeso bhagavato paṭissutvā vihārapacchāyāyaṃ āsanaṃ paññapesi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Sīha, and he did so. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "dn6:4.9"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vihārā nikkhamma vihārapacchāyāyaṃ paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha came out of his dwelling and sat in the shade of the dwelling on the seat spread out. "

#. REF: pts-cs5
msgctxt "dn6:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho te kosalakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā māgadhakā ca brāhmaṇadūtā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then the brahmin emissaries went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "dn6:5.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "dn6:5.3"
msgid "Oṭṭhaddhopi licchavī mahatiyā licchavīparisāya saddhiṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho oṭṭhaddho licchavī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: “purimāni, bhante, divasāni purimatarāni sunakkhatto licchaviputto yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Oṭṭhaddha the Licchavi together with a large assembly of Licchavis also went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Oṭṭhaddha said to the Buddha, “Sir, a few days ago Sunakkhatta the Licchavi came to me and said: "

msgctxt "dn6:5.4"
msgid "‘yadagge ahaṃ, mahāli, bhagavantaṃ upanissāya viharāmi, na ciraṃ tīṇi vassāni, dibbāni hi kho rūpāni passāmi piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, no ca kho dibbāni saddāni suṇāmi piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyānī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Mahāli, soon I will have been living in dependence on the Buddha for three years. I see heavenly sights that are pleasant, sensual, and arousing, but I don’t hear heavenly sounds that are pleasant, sensual, and arousing.’ "

msgctxt "dn6:5.5"
msgid "Santāneva nu kho, bhante, sunakkhatto licchaviputto dibbāni saddāni nāssosi piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, udāhu asantānī”ti? "
msgstr "The heavenly sounds that Sunakkhatta cannot hear: do such sounds really exist or not?” "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn6:5.6"
msgid "2.1. Ekaṃsabhāvitasamādhi "
msgstr "2.1. One-Sided Immersion "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "dn6:5.7"
msgid "“Santāneva kho, mahāli, sunakkhatto licchaviputto dibbāni saddāni nāssosi piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, no asantānī”ti. "
msgstr "“Such sounds really do exist, but Sunakkhatta cannot hear them.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs6
msgctxt "dn6:6.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena santāneva sunakkhatto licchaviputto dibbāni saddāni nāssosi piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, no asantānī”ti? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why Sunakkhatta cannot hear them, even though they really do exist?” "

# NOTE: RD’s translation of this passage is much more satisfactory than MW’s.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.153, sc9
msgctxt "dn6:6.2"
msgid "“Idha, mahāli, bhikkhuno puratthimāya disāya ekaṃsabhāvito samādhi hoti dibbānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, no ca kho dibbānaṃ saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "“Mahāli, take a mendicant who has developed one-sided immersion to the eastern quarter so as to see heavenly sights but not to hear heavenly sounds. "

msgctxt "dn6:6.3"
msgid "So puratthimāya disāya ekaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, no ca kho dibbānaṃ saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "When they have developed immersion for that purpose, "

msgctxt "dn6:6.4"
msgid "Puratthimāya disāya dibbāni rūpāni passati piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, no ca kho dibbāni saddāni suṇāti piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni. "
msgstr "they see heavenly sights but don’t hear heavenly sounds. "

msgctxt "dn6:6.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn6:6.6"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, mahāli, hoti bhikkhuno puratthimāya disāya ekaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, no ca kho dibbānaṃ saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "Because that is how it is for a mendicant who develops immersion in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs7, sc10
msgctxt "dn6:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, mahāli, bhikkhuno dakkhiṇāya disāya … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, take a mendicant who has developed one-sided immersion to the southern quarter … "

msgctxt "dn6:7.2"
msgid "pacchimāya disāya … "
msgstr "western quarter … "

msgctxt "dn6:7.3"
msgid "uttarāya disāya … "
msgstr "northern quarter … "

msgctxt "dn6:7.4"
msgid "uddhamadho tiriyaṃ ekaṃsabhāvito samādhi hoti dibbānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, no ca kho dibbānaṃ saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "above, below, across … "

msgctxt "dn6:7.5"
msgid "So uddhamadho tiriyaṃ ekaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, no ca kho dibbānaṃ saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:7.6"
msgid "Uddhamadho tiriyaṃ dibbāni rūpāni passati piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, no ca kho dibbāni saddāni suṇāti piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:7.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:7.8"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, mahāli, hoti bhikkhuno uddhamadho tiriyaṃ ekaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, no ca kho dibbānaṃ saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
