#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs10, pts-vp-pli1.155, sc13
msgctxt "dn6:10.1"
msgid "Idha, mahāli, bhikkhuno puratthimāya disāya ubhayaṃsabhāvito samādhi hoti dibbānañca rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ dibbānañca saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "Take a mendicant who has developed two-sided immersion to the eastern quarter so as to both hear heavenly sounds and see heavenly sights. "

msgctxt "dn6:10.2"
msgid "So puratthimāya disāya ubhayaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānañca rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, dibbānañca saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "When they have developed immersion for that purpose, "

msgctxt "dn6:10.3"
msgid "Puratthimāya disāya dibbāni ca rūpāni passati piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, dibbāni ca saddāni suṇāti piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni. "
msgstr "they both see heavenly sights and hear heavenly sounds. "

msgctxt "dn6:10.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn6:10.5"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, mahāli, hoti bhikkhuno puratthimāya disāya ubhayaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānañca rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ dibbānañca saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "Because that is how it is for a mendicant who develops immersion in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs11, sc14
msgctxt "dn6:11.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, mahāli, bhikkhuno dakkhiṇāya disāya … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, take a mendicant who has developed two-sided immersion to the southern quarter … "

msgctxt "dn6:11.2"
msgid "pacchimāya disāya … "
msgstr "western quarter … "

msgctxt "dn6:11.3"
msgid "uttarāya disāya … "
msgstr "northern quarter … "

msgctxt "dn6:11.4"
msgid "uddhamadho tiriyaṃ ubhayaṃsabhāvito samādhi hoti dibbānañca rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, dibbānañca saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "above, below, across … "

msgctxt "dn6:11.5"
msgid "So uddhamadho tiriyaṃ ubhayaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānañca rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ dibbānañca saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:11.6"
msgid "Uddhamadho tiriyaṃ dibbāni ca rūpāni passati piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, dibbāni ca saddāni suṇāti piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:11.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:11.8"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, mahāli, hoti bhikkhuno uddhamadho tiriyaṃ ubhayaṃsabhāvite samādhimhi dibbānañca rūpānaṃ dassanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ, dibbānañca saddānaṃ savanāya piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ. "
msgstr "That is how it is for a mendicant who develops immersion in that way. "

msgctxt "dn6:11.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, mahāli, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena santāneva sunakkhatto licchaviputto dibbāni saddāni nāssosi piyarūpāni kāmūpasaṃhitāni rajanīyāni, no asantānī”ti. "
msgstr "This is the cause, Mahāli, this is the reason why Sunakkhatta cannot hear heavenly sounds that are pleasant, sensual, and arousing, even though they really do exist.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs12, pts-vp-pli1.156, sc15
msgctxt "dn6:12.1"
msgid "“Etāsaṃ nūna, bhante, samādhibhāvanānaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti. "
msgstr "“Surely the mendicants must live the spiritual life under the Buddha for the sake of realizing such a development of immersion?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:12.2"
msgid "“Na kho, mahāli, etāsaṃ samādhibhāvanānaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti. "
msgstr "“No, Mahāli, the mendicants don’t live the spiritual life under me for the sake of realizing such a development of immersion. "

msgctxt "dn6:12.3"
msgid "Atthi kho, mahāli, aññeva dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca, yesaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti. "
msgstr "There are other things that are finer, for the sake of which the mendicants live the spiritual life under me.” "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn6:12.4"
msgid "2.2. Catuariyaphala "
msgstr "2.2. The Four Noble Fruits "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs13, sc16
msgctxt "dn6:13.1"
msgid "“Katame pana te, bhante, dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca, yesaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what are those finer things?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:13.2"
msgid "“Idha, mahāli, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "“Firstly, Mahāli, with the ending of three fetters a mendicant is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "

msgctxt "dn6:13.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahāli, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca, yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti. "
msgstr "This is one of the finer things for the sake of which the mendicants live the spiritual life under me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
#. VAR: sakideva → sakiṃdeva (mr)
msgctxt "dn6:13.4"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, mahāli, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant—with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion—is a once-returner. They come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering. "

msgctxt "dn6:13.5"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahāli, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca, yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti. "
msgstr "This too is one of the finer things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "dn6:13.6"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, mahāli, bhikkhu pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti, tattha parinibbāyī, anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā. "
msgstr "Furthermore, with the ending of the five lower fetters, a mendicant is reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world. "

msgctxt "dn6:13.7"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahāli, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca, yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti. "
msgstr "This too is one of the finer things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "dn6:13.8"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, mahāli, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "dn6:13.9"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahāli, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca, yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti. "
msgstr "This too is one of the finer things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:13.10"
msgid "Ime kho te, mahāli, dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca, yesaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the finer things, for the sake of which the mendicants live the spiritual life under me.” "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn6:13.11"
msgid "2.3. Ariyaaṭṭhaṅgikamagga "
msgstr "2.3. The Noble Eightfold Path "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs14, sc20
msgctxt "dn6:14.1"
msgid "“Atthi pana, bhante, maggo atthi paṭipadā etesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāyā”ti? "
msgstr "“But, sir, is there a path and a practice for realizing these things?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:14.2"
msgid "“Atthi kho, mahāli, maggo atthi paṭipadā etesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“There is, Mahāli.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.157, sc21
msgctxt "dn6:14.3"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, maggo katamā paṭipadā etesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāyā”ti? "
msgstr "“Well, what is it?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:14.4"
msgid "“Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo. "
msgstr "“It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "dn6:14.5"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo sammāsati sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

msgctxt "dn6:14.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, mahāli, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā etesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya. "
msgstr "This is the path and the practice for realizing these things. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn6:14.7"
msgid "2.4. Dvepabbajitavatthu "
msgstr "2.4. On the Two Renunciates "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs15, sc22
msgctxt "dn6:15.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, mahāli, samayaṃ kosambiyaṃ viharāmi ghositārāme. "
msgstr "This one time, Mahāli, I was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. "

msgctxt "dn6:15.2"
msgid "Atha kho dve pabbajitā—"
msgstr "Then two renunciates—"

# NOTE: Contra MW, text does not say both were paribbajaka. Again, RD is more accurate.
msgctxt "dn6:15.3"
msgid "muṇḍiyo ca paribbājako jāliyo ca dārupattikantevāsī yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. upasaṅkamitvā mayā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu. "
msgstr "the wanderer Muṇḍiya and Jāliya the pupil of Dārupattika—came and exchanged greetings with me. "

msgctxt "dn6:15.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho te dve pabbajitā maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they stood to one side and said to me: "

msgctxt "dn6:15.5"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso gotama, taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ, udāhu aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend Gotama, are the soul and the body the same thing, or they are different things?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs16, sc23
msgctxt "dn6:16.1"
msgid "‘Tena hāvuso, suṇātha sādhukaṃ manasi karotha bhāsissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Well then, reverends, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:16.2"
msgid "‘Evamāvuso’ti kho te dve pabbajitā mama paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "‘Yes, reverend,’ they replied. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:16.3"
msgid "Ahaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "I said this: "

msgctxt "dn6:16.4"
msgid "‘idhāvuso tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe … "
msgstr "‘Take the case when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha … "

msgctxt "dn6:16.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.158, sc24
msgctxt "dn6:16.6"
msgid "… pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn6:16.7"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "They enter and remain in the first absorption. "

#. VAR: kallaṃ → na kallaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn6:16.8"
msgid "Yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of them: "

# NOTE: Take care of quote nesting: MS is wrong.
msgctxt "dn6:16.9"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti? "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:16.10"
msgid "Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "‘It would, reverend.’ "

msgctxt "dn6:16.11"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā, ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:16.12"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi. "
msgstr "‘But reverends, I know and see like this. "

msgctxt "dn6:16.13"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi: "
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say: "

msgctxt "dn6:16.14"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā … pe … "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs17
msgctxt "dn6:17.1"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "They enter and remain in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "dn6:17.2"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "dn6:17.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "dn6:17.4"
msgid "Yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of them: "

msgctxt "dn6:17.5"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti? "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:17.6"
msgid "Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "‘It would, reverend.’ "

msgctxt "dn6:17.7"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:17.8"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi. "
msgstr "‘But reverends, I know and see like this. "

msgctxt "dn6:17.9"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi: "
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say: "

msgctxt "dn6:17.10"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā … pe … "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs18
msgctxt "dn6:18.1"
msgid "ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti … "
msgstr "They extend and project the mind toward knowledge and vision … "

msgctxt "dn6:18.2"
msgid "yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of them: "

msgctxt "dn6:18.3"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti? "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”?’ "

msgctxt "dn6:18.4"
msgid "… pe … "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:18.5"
msgid "Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "‘It would, reverend.’ "

msgctxt "dn6:18.6"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:18.7"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi. "
msgstr "‘But reverends, I know and see like this. "

msgctxt "dn6:18.8"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi: "
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say: "

msgctxt "dn6:18.9"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā. … pe … "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs19, sc25
msgctxt "dn6:19.1"
msgid "Nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: “… there is no return to any state of existence.” "

msgctxt "dn6:19.2"
msgid "Yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of them: "

msgctxt "dn6:19.3"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti? "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:19.4"
msgid "Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati na kallaṃ tassetaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "‘It would not, reverend.’ "

msgctxt "dn6:19.5"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn6:19.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi. "
msgstr "‘But reverends, I know and see like this. "

msgctxt "dn6:19.7"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi: "
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say: "

msgctxt "dn6:19.8"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā”ti. "
msgstr "“The soul and the body are the same thing” or “The soul and the body are different things”.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "dn6:19.9"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "dn6:19.10"
msgid "Attamano oṭṭhaddho licchavī bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Oṭṭhaddha the Licchavi was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn6:19.11"
msgid "Mahālisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

